    <h2>What is <%= site_name %>?</h2>
    <p><%= site_name %> is a community-driven project that aims to bring transparency to the privacy and security of online services.</p>
    <p>New web applications, site and services go live everyday, and more of our lives is being put online. New companies barely a few months old are suddenly entrusted with your personal data. Long established services may have a history of privacy breaches or unsatisfactory behaviour with regards to safeguarding your personal data.</p>
    <p><%= site_name %> is a way to bring this information together to allow you to make an informed choice on whether to use a service, or which of several competing services to use. Most services are happy to shout about their amazing features and this site aims to bridge the gap between the marketing material and reality.</p>
    <hr/>

    <h2>Our mission</h2>
    <ul>
      <li class="mission">Promote internet security awareness</li>
      <li class="mission">Encourage transparency from services regarding their security implementations and how they handle personal data</li>
      <li class="mission">Provide a tool that allows people to make better informed decisions regarding their personal data</li>
      <li class="mission">Give service owners the opportunity to address issues that the public is not happy with</li>
    </ul>
    <hr/>

    <h2>Community-driven you say?</h2>

    <h6 class="mission">Independent</h6>
    <p><%= site_name %> is an independent project, not linked to any companies. It was created by people that want to see improvements in the security of online services and acts in the interest of the community.</p>

    <h6 class="mission">Open Source</h6>
    <p>This source code to this site is fully open sourced and is available on our <a href="http://github.com">Github</a> page.</p>
    <p>All <%= site_name %> material is release under the <a href="#">Badger License</a>.</p>

    <h6 class="mission">Moderators</h6>
    <p>In order to prevent abuse such as spam, misuse or biased reports, services and related data go through a process of moderation.</p>

    <h6 class="mission">Services added by users just like you</h6>
    <p>If you can't find the service you're looking for, you can help contribute by logging in and adding the it. Fill in as much detail as possible, and the moderates will take care of the rest.</p>

    <h6 class="mission">Transparent</h6>
    <p>We try to set the standard, so every aspect of this site is as open as possible.</p>
